column5: Root block of a file (has not been used so far).
The information about the acquisition details.
Used within evoked block to include one aspect of evoked responses like standard average, alternating average, standard error of mean etc.
Result of a HPI fitting procedure.
Data acquired from one HPI coil.
Information about the project under which the data were acquired.
Continuous data is processed raw data.
Nothing, reserved space, invalidated data etc.
Information about the events detected on the trigger channels during data acquisition.
An index of file id/file name pairs.
Raw data collected with Internal Active Shielding.
Evoked data collected with Internal Active Shielding.
Data about HPI subsystem structure and coding of related data bits.
Data about phantom subsystem structure and coding of related data bits.
Data about system status items and coding of related data bits.
Volume data, e.g. MRI/CT set, segmentation etc.
Slice of a volume, e.g. MRI/CT image
A set of related (in DICOM terminology `secondary capture') images like the 3D renderings of the brain surface.
A spherically symmetric volume conductor description.
One or more conductor model descriptions.
One set of vectors of the SSP data.
Auxiliary data created by the source modelling program XFit.
Processing history. Can contain multiple processing_record's
